snippet.textDisplay:
Take it or leave it, the word behind the lines in the UFC managerial
office had been leaked to suggest that Conor was promised a knockout win
over Cerone in order to try to solidify his brand name once again and
to make him a valid contender. A loss would have devastated PPV sales,
the revenue base, and endorsements. This was a brainstorm idea that was
set in place by UFC brass in order to keep their "cash-cow" viable.
Conor brings in an entire country of sales with him from all over the
world that could be estimated to gross millions of dollars. The UFC will
be very careful about how they match Conor up in the future with other
opponents for this very reason only. The UFC is a business and it needs
the influx of cash on a regular basis in order to stay afloat. As Conor
falls from notariety so will the revenue base of the UFC fall with him.
Interrogate Cerone and get the real truth.

snippet.textDisplay:
It's tiring to listen to these phoney questions about violence: Hollywood produce more violence every year than an entire UFC season,
you have more violent offences and actions conducted by law enforcement and 3-letters government agencies around the world and
I am not even talking about crimes and offences committed by 'normal' people.
Our world and most of its societies, cultures and species are violent by nature, that's a fact. That's why ritualised violence acts such as
the MMA or any sports in general are just a symbolic rehearsal of what even kinder-garden kids know for fact: the human species is violent
by nature. It doesn't mean I condone violence at large or think it solves problems in general but I think combat sports and martial arts have
done more to address this human truth by channelling this impulse into a regulated activity than any media or political quacks.
If you think I am making it up, just read any newspapers you can put your hands on for a day.

snippet.textDisplay: We all have seen the best of the best fall and never get the “eye of the tiger” back. We all say it and see it. I admit, I did too. But knowing the back story of Connor and what he believes about manifesting, affirmations, and the law of attraction....then to see Tony Robbins walk into the octogon, you can believe that this is going to be one of those very rare instances where someone who is a legend becomes a GOD. I am excited to see this man be that person who defies the odds of fighting the demons of self doubt after you have been at the top. You cannot be the greatest forever and that is the facts of life. But the facts of life are also we love the underdog story and we love the comeback story. Watching C-McC (I just made that up) fight is both exciting and gut wrenching. Perhaps like the world watching astronauts land on the moon. As a witness of the times we are so fortunate to see humans like this to inspire us to overcome our own personal battles by comparing ourselves to the greats of human potential. Watching C-McC grow from a hungry young pimply faced boy to a cocky champion and now to a humble warrior is my favorite part. Don;t you agree? #LifeTheresAnAppForThat
